label aletta_audrey_lavish_shiori_male_ending:

    if renpy.has_label("office_harem_achievement_3") and not game.flags.cheat:
        call office_harem_achievement_3 from _call_office_harem_achievement_3
    $ game.room = "church"
    scene bg church wedding
    "You know, I don't even remember what my plan was when I landed my current job."
    "Whether I was planning on climbing the ladder there, going as far as I could go."
    "Or if it was just supposed to be a job to pay the bills until I got something better."
    "But I'm pretty sure it wasn't the place I thought I'd meet my future partners in life!"
    "The best I can remember is that I was just planning on having some fun around the office."
    "You know, slacking off and relieving the stress of work by indulging with my co-workers."
    "But one thing lead to another, and now here I am."
    "I'm standing at the altar, waiting for those same co-workers to come join me."
    "I could never have predicted that this was going to end in me getting married."
    "Even less so that it would be to more than one of the girls I work with!"
    "Not that I'm complaining, you understand?"
    "I'm very happy to be where I am right now."
    "It's just that my life kind of feels like a roller-coaster at the moment!"
    "Trying to take my mind off it, I glance around the chapel."
    "The place is done up nicely, which is a miracle in and of itself."
    "Believe me, when you have more than one girl picking out the decor, it gets heated!"
    "The pews are full to bursting with guests, again to be expected with more than one bride."
    "I recognise some of the face that are looking at me as I scan one row after another."
    "But how can I be expected to recognise everyone out there?"
    "Everyone involved in this wedding brings along a crowd of their own guests."
    "Telling who belongs to who is almost impossible!"
    "I'm already thinking about asking the girls for photographs and notes on their families."
    "And that's when the music begins to play, filling the chapel with sound."
    "Of course I snap out of it and straighten myself up, almost standing to attention."
    "How could I fail to recognise that music and what it signifies?"
    "I was right in the middle of everyone fighting over what they'd come down the aisle to!"
    "But then the memory of that last squabble and how a compromise was reached seems to vanish."
    "Because all I can see is the girls as they sweep into the chapel and down the aisle."
    show aletta wedding at mostleft4
    "Aletta comes first, like she's leading the procession."
    "She has her head held high like a queen."
    "And I can feel my heart beating faster at the mere sight of her."
    if aletta.pregnant:
        "I hardly notice the fact that she's pregnant."
        "The dress she's chosen is so well cut that it's almost hidden."
        "Almost, but not quite, and I guess that's what makes the difference."
    show audrey wedding at mostright4
    "Audrey somehow manages to walk with the others and yet still stand apart."
    "She has a slightly snarky, ironic smile on her face."
    "But she still looks elegant and beautiful in her dress."
    if audrey.pregnant:
        "Audrey holds her bouquet on top of her bump."
        "Almost like she's trying to show it off to the world."
        "I should have known that she'd be that bold and unashamed!"
    show lavish wedding at left4
    "Lavish walks towards me with that same quiet confidence she always has."
    "Her dress is understated and so makes her beauty all the more plain to see."
    "I never know how she can say so much without speaking a single word."
    if lavish.pregnant:
        "I almost forget that she's pregnant and already showing."
        "But then I notice the delicate curve of her belly."
        "And the sight of it reminds me how much I love her."
    show shiori wedding at right4
    "Shiori comes last in the procession, but my eyes linger on her the longest."
    "Of course she looks simply beautiful in her dress."
    "But what really matters to me is the fact that she's smiling."
    "And I feel a surge of happiness knowing that she's happy too."
    if shiori.pregnant:
        "Maybe that has something to do with the sight of her belly too?"
        "At a stroke we're getting married and starting a new family together."
        "This really is the beginning of a new life for all of us!"
    "I shuffle awkwardly to the side as the girls reach the altar."
    "And one by one they come to stand beside me, all moving here and there."
    "I mean sure, we tried to tackle all of this at the rehearsal the other day."
    "But I think nerves are playing a part as everyone jostles for space."
    "Once we all have enough room, smiles and glances are exchanged."
    "I can see that each one of the girls is in the same state as me."
    "That strange mixture of excitement and almost dread that give you butterflies!"
    "Priest" "Ahem..."
    "As one we all look up and towards the priest."
    "And he gestures that the ceremony is about to begin."
    "I'm glad that he takes such firm control of the proceedings."
    "Because all of a sudden, we're focused and following instructions."
    "Priest" "Dearly beloved..."
    "Priest" "We are gathered here today..."
    "Priest" "To join these people - and I do mean ALL of them!"
    "There's a ripple of laughter from the guests at the little joke."
    "But then the priest presses on and they fall silent again."
    "Priest" "In the bonds of holy matrimony..."
    "The rest of the ceremony goes pretty much as you'd imagine."
    "Why, what were you expecting would happen?"
    "Conjuring demons and animal sacrifices?"
    "The only difference from any other wedding is that everything gets said more than twice."
    "Priest" "Do you, Aletta, take these people..."
    "Priest" "To be your lawful, wedded partners?"
    show aletta happy
    aletta.say "I do."
    "Priest" "Do you, Audrey, take these people..."
    "Priest" "To be your lawful, wedded partners?"
    show audrey happy
    audrey.say "I do."
    "Priest" "Do you, Lavish, take these people..."
    "Priest" "To be your lawful, wedded partners?"
    show lavish happy
    lavish.say "I do."
    "Priest" "Do you, Shiori, take these people..."
    "Priest" "To be your lawful, wedded partners?"
    show shiori happy
    shiori.say "I do."
    "Priest" "And finally..."
    "Priest" "Do you, [hero.name], take these people..."
    "Priest" "To be your lawful, wedded partners?"
    mike.say "I do."
    "The priest nods, taking a moment to catch his breath."
    "Priest" "I call upon those here present..."
    "Priest" "That if you know of any lawful reason these people may not be married..."
    "Priest" "Speak now, or forever hold your peace!"
    "There's the customary pause as people chuckle and glance around."
    "Maybe they expect an army of angry exes to storm the chapel in that moment."
    "But thankfully nothing that outlandish happens."
    "Priest" "Very well..."
    "Priest" "I therefore pronounce you married."
    "Priest" "You may...erm..."
    "Priest" "Well...do something appropriate, I suppose!"
    "We come together in a group hug as the priest says this."
    "Everyone intertwining their arms and hugging each other."
    "I guess our relationship is a little like that."
